Let me explain one by one.
Prompt has `Read "Hints" carefully if it exists.`.
So LLM try to find Hint. But there is no hint in prompt. So LLM retry to find it through all messages. But there is no any hint, too. And then LLM noticed Hint is not provided.
As you can see, inference messages are too long. In short, token is too large. So, small update of prompt is helpful for LLM.
`if it exists`
So LLM try to find it.
And if token of prompt+messages is too large, llm often ignores the 3 words.
it passes in as hints: ""
Even though we mention all instructions in the prompt, the LLM is not able to understand all the instructions, that's why LLM fails
Therefore, we need to remove any of useless part from prompts and tools to avoid confusions for LLM
its in the leading part of the prompt, which mdoels over index on

This is one of the basic principle of prompt engineering

When I work for teaching LLMs, if we simplify prompt, the LLM solves the problem but if we add some unnecessary part to the prompt, the LLM often confuses
